<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    wisc.edu domain name changes
From:       <a href="?a=95837785000016&r=1&w=2">cole () cs ! wisc ! edu (Bruce Cole)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198712">1987-12-09 16:06:44</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927086&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927086&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


On December 15th, the host names of all University of Wisconsin - Madison
Computer Sciences Department machines will change from host.wisc.edu to
host.cs.wisc.edu.  The host names of all Statistics Department machines will
change from host.wisc.edu to host.stat.wisc.edu.  The current host names for
these machines will continue to work for several more months, but will be
removed from the NIC's host tables eventually.

Please update the mailing lists you maintain to use the new host names.  These
new host names already exist in the NIC's host tables as aliases, so there
should not be problems with the timing of your changes.  The Statistics
Department hosts can be differentiated from the Computer Science Department
hosts by looking at the host aliases in the host tables.  Statistics Department
hosts will have aliases of the form host.stat.wisc.edu.

Note that the host names cs.wisc.edu and stat.wisc.edu will not be affected
by the changeover.

Problems/questions to postmaster@cs.wisc.edu.

